    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Validation_CheckUploadDataSummary",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to validate uploaded billing data against a coversheet for a specific billing period. It retrieves the current billing period, calculates the total billed amount, therms, and CCF (hundred cubic feet) from the uploaded data, and checks if these values match the corresponding values in the coversheet. If there is a discrepancy, it raises an error indicating that the data does not match."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including querying for the current billing period, aggregating data from a billing adjustment table, and performing a validation check against another table. The logic is straightforward but involves multiple database operations, making it moderately complex."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This stored procedure does not take any input parameters. It operates based on the current processing period and the data available in the relevant tables."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Retrieve Current Billing Period",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure starts by declaring a variable "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@BillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and assigns it the current billing period from the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Billing.ApplicationTimeFrame",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table where "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "CurrentProcessingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is 'Y'."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Aggregate Uploaded Data",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": It declares variables "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@therms",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@ccf",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@billedAmount",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to store aggregated values. It calculates these values by summing up the respective columns from the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ConEd.UploadConEdisonAccountBillingAdjustmentGas",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table. It uses "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ISNULL",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to handle potential null values in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "CancelTotalTherms",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "CancelTotalCCF",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Validation Check",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure checks if there is a record in the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "ConEd.ConEdCoversheet",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " table that matches the calculated values for the current billing period. If no matching record is found, it sets an error message and raises an error with severity level 12."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
